Package de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.control

Provides interfaces for marking the behaviour of instructions with regard to the control-flow.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
JumpAlways Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will always lead to a jump in the control flow.
JumpConditional Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will lead to a jump in the control flow under a specified condition (if).
JumpException Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that can throw an exception which will disrupt the control flow.
JumpInvocation Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will invoke another method.
JumpNever Interface that is to be implemented by any instruction that will never lead to a jump in the control flow.
JumpSwitching Interface that is to be implemented by a switching operation (lookupswitch or tableswitch).
 

Package de.wwu.muggl.instructions.interfaces.control Description
